HEADWORD: Melton
<hw>Mel"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A kind of stout woolen cloth with unfinished face
and without raised nap. A commoner variety has a cotton warp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

